d default password behavior\n- `UserDetailsServiceAutoConfiguration` default `InMemoryUserDetailsManager`\n- backing off when a custom `UserDetailsService` is provided\n- servlet security auto-configuration default `SecurityFilterChain`\n- `DelegatingFilterProxyRegistrationBean` order, filter name, and dispatcher types\n- backing off when a custom `SecurityFilterChain` is provided\n- servlet `PathRequest` static resource matchers, including exclusions and selected locations\n- `SecurityFilterProperties` defaults and setters\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0129e3f9087b66fb016a3eed815b48819384e255e8968706a0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 636, "output": 1043, "cacheRead": 45568, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47247, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782508914774, "responseId": "resp_0129e3f9087b66fb016a3eed7356348193a56eea863eca6726"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Spring Security's Configuration**\n\nI’m considering how @EnableWebSecurity in Spring Security works. It seems that it doesn’t add form login unless there’s a default config bean in Spring Boot, which is interesting. Actually, does the default filter chain get generated by Spring Security if there isn’t a defined chain? But we definitely could provide one; that’s an important detail to keep in mind. I’ll need to clarify this further as I dive deeper.\n\n**Considering spring security bindings**\n\nI need to check in relation to `spring.security.filter.dispatcher-types=request,error`, as it seems that the binder for Set<Boot DispatcherType> expects enum values. Maybe using lower-case could work? Boot relaxed binding seems to handle that. I noticed a potential warning about client/server timeouts and the implications of direct internet access. It might require `requestMatcherContextRunner`, and I want to ensure that the `WebApplicationContextUtils.getRequiredWebApplicationContext` operates correctly. Finally, I'll mention the modified file, as no tests were run.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0129e3f9087b66fb016a3eed74040c819386e0e18dffbd3d08\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPu2BtjYOLKeljhua-yV7tmaLTVEKcz4GJrYDQNsVo_8RmAAwux6DdY66V4O08zvl3RYmpqLEjRJuz32m2W11UIaFOz7E7eB59DujmUTegJAvlq2AzHKHZTql-6aUbdHGepWUVGlgkILZF2CALGpIFnvwhBjRGIj_lVS6DB6_gAO_kZ2_kdm1KJGgcXKh3jLIHaMiffwlWc4TmRzuohK9v1TRXXuYN4Qt984EXE7iz7pncE7x-NpfEkLOROmiqMIHvOssqkoaNwdJlPPcv_w9uMfLYfk-3OnZkHileqgHBaBTsC61vYfPrGOXiZWg-7z_lzEg623wsQLiSkrDqhfaWdIare9UYyoNlR3EyJLTWY9GjnaUggD6GwQzxgiQc0lFozg4uVz7EF7axaqQd8toKcm77Q1JNcRpcjBCJIhSin8L-FzSxIxNLk22bmzhBG3JPejN1asvL5r8LzPOzB4rI6JMdWQAzWJwQ9cgIVQH5Rwjnkko2Ss1d5SIy-CPXYksEf15U9ymvPnfntwRGOu2TqQrMQs7HFhYI2JbTA4Q_PNCD69Jmu1IIq6LPa1Yr05AWjz6P0ZO7MmUkXurOtMj1Alu9awjOS0Xf951hL5oggG4E4cRIgjIDkjvl-jO400u7zoOM